iances"></span><h2 class=3D"lt-stats-27814 editable" style=3D"background-co=
lor: unset;">9.5.2 Hypothesis Test for Two Variances</h2>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">Sometimes we=
 will need to compare the variation or standard deviation between two group=
s. For example, let=E2=80=99s say that the average delivery time for two lo=
cations of the same company is the same but we hear complaint of inconsiste=
nt delivery times for one location. We can use an F-test to see if the stan=
dard deviations for the two locations was different.</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">There are th=
ree types of hypothesis tests for comparing the ratio of two population var=
iances , see Figure 9-14.</p>

<p class=3D"mt-align-center lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unse=
t;"><img alt=3D"clipboard_ed1db703c4df0cff23ec4046f11dd1ccd.png" class=3D"i=
nternal" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://stats.libretexts.org/@api/deki/fil=
es/18169/clipboard_ed1db703c4df0cff23ec4046f11dd1ccd.png?revision=3D1"></p>

<p class=3D"mt-align-center lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unse=
t;">Figure 9-14</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">If we take t=
he square root of the variance, we get a standard deviation. Therefore, tak=
ing the square root of both sides of the hypotheses, we can also use the sa=
me test for standard deviations. We use the following notation for the hypo=
theses.</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">There are 3 =
types of hypothesis tests for comparing the population standard deviations =
=CF=83<sub>1</sub><sub>/</sub>=CF=83<sub>2</sub>, see Figure 9-15.</p>

<p class=3D"mt-align-center lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unse=
t;"><img alt=3D"clipboard_eb049b72cbfb13e29521bfb93f270c305.png" class=3D"i=
nternal" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://stats.libretexts.org/@api/deki/fil=
es/18170/clipboard_eb049b72cbfb13e29521bfb93f270c305.png?revision=3D1"></p>

<p class=3D"mt-align-center lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unse=
t;">Figure 9-15</p>

