<p>A researcher is studying the variability in electricity (in kilowatt hou=
rs) people from two different cities use in their homes. Random samples of =
17 days in Sacramento and 16 days in Portland are given below. Test to see =
if there is a difference in the variance of electricity use between the two=
 cities at =CE=B1 =3D 0.10. Assume that electricity use is normally distrib=
uted, use the p-value method.</p>

