<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">Use technolo=
gy to compute the standard deviations and sample sizes. Enter the Sacrament=
o data into list 1, then do 1-Var Stats L1 and you should get s<sub>1</sub>=
 =3D 163.2362 and n<sub>1</sub> =3D 17. Enter the Portland data into list 2=
, then do 1-Var Stats L2 and you should get s<sub>2</sub> =3D 179.3957 and =
n<sub>2</sub> =3D 16. Alternatively, use Excel=E2=80=99s descriptive statis=
tics.</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">The test sta=
tistic is</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">The p-value =
would be double the area to the left of F =3D 0.82796 (Use double the area =
to the right if the test statistic is &gt; 1).</p>

<p class=3D"mt-align-center lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unse=
t;"><img alt=3D"clipboard_ef9a8e4c8ae93fc9217e1278519ea7848.png" class=3D"i=
nternal" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://stats.libretexts.org/@api/deki/fil=
es/18174/clipboard_ef9a8e4c8ae93fc9217e1278519ea7848.png?revision=3D1"></p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">Using the TI=
 calculator Fcdf(0,0.82796,16,15).</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">In Excel we =
get the p-value =3D2*F.DIST(E8,E7,F7,TRUE) =3D 0.7106.</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">Since the p-=
value is greater than alpha, we would fail to reject H<sub>0</sub>.</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;">There is no =
statistically significant difference between variance of electricity use be=
tween Sacramento and Portland.</p>

<p class=3D"lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unset;"><strong>Exce=
l:</strong> When you have raw data, you can use Excel to find all this info=
rmation using the Data Analysis tool. Enter the data into Excel, then choos=
e Data &gt; Data Analysis &gt; F-Test: Two Sample for Variances.</p>

<p class=3D"mt-align-center lt-stats-27814" style=3D"background-color: unse=
